{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Layout","images":[{"identifier":"Page.png","type":"card"}],"role":"article","color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"blue"},"modules":[{"name":"KeyboardKitPro"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A flexible keyboard layout is an important part of a software keyboard, and must consider many factors like the current locale, device, screen orientation, user preferences, etc.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In KeyboardKit, an ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet","isActive":true},{"text":" is used to create a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout"},{"text":", where the input set specifies input keys and the layout specifies the full keyboard layout.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayoutProvider"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol that is implemented by classes that can provide dynamic layouts, as well as many base classes that provide standard layouts that can be customized."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"👑 "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","isActive":true},{"text":" unlocks localized input sets and layout providers for all locales, as well as additional input sets like ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet\/qwertz"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet\/azerty","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", and support for iPad Pro. Information about Pro features can be found at the end of this article.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Input Sets","anchor":"Input-Sets","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet"},{"text":" set specifies the input keys of a keyboard. It makes it easy to define different input keys for the same keyboard layout.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit comes with some pre-defined input sets, like "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet\/qwerty"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet\/numeric(currency:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet\/symbolic(currencies:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Keyboard layouts","anchor":"Keyboard-layouts","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" specifies the full set of keys om a keyboard. Layouts vary greatly for different device types, screen orientations, locales, keyboard configurations, etc."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For instance, most iOS keyboards have 3 input key rows, where the input keys are surrounded by actions, as well as a bottom row with a space key and contextual action and input keys."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is however not always true. Most layouts are different on iPhone and iPad, and many locales make changes to the entire layout, not just inputs. For instance, Armenian keyboards use 4 rows, Arabic keyboards remove some action buttons, etc.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Keyboard-layout-providers","text":"Keyboard layout providers","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Given all this, the layout engine has to be flexible. KeyboardKit has a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayoutProvider","type":"reference"},{"text":" that generates layouts at runtime, based on many different factors. Layout providers can use any information to tweak any part of a layout at any time.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit automatically creates an instance of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/StandardProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and injects it into "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController\/services","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". You can replace it at any time, as described further down, or inject localized providers into it."}]},{"anchor":"How-to-create-a-custom-provider","text":"How to create a custom provider","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can create a custom layout provider to customize the layout for certain locales or devices, or to provide a completely custom layout.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can implement ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayoutProvider","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" from scratch, or inherit and customize any of the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/StandardProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/BaseProvider","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/DeviceBasedProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/iPadProvider"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/iPadProProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/iPhoneProvider"},{"type":"text","text":" base classes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For instance, here’s a custom provider that inherits ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/StandardProvider","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", then injects a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardAction\/tab","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" key into the layout:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["class CustomKeyboardLayoutProvider: KeyboardLayout.StandardProvider {","    ","    override func keyboardLayout(for context: KeyboardContext) -> KeyboardLayout {","        let layout = super.keyboardLayout(for: context)","        var rows = layout.itemRows","        var row = layout.itemRows[0]","        let next = row[0]","        let size = KeyboardLayout.ItemSize(width: .available, height: next.size.height)","        let tab = KeyboardLayout.Item(action: .tab, size: size, insets: next.insets)","        row.insert(tab, at: 0)","        rows[0] = row","        layout.itemRows = rows","        return layout","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To use this provider instead of the standard one, just inject it into ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController\/services"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["class KeyboardViewController: KeyboardInputViewController {","","    override func viewDidLoad() {","        services.layoutProvider = CustomKeyboardLayoutProvider()","        super.viewDidLoad()","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will make KeyboardKit use your custom implementation instead of the standard one.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"👑 KeyboardKit Pro","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"👑-KeyboardKit-Pro"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro"}],"overridingTitle":"KeyboardKit Pro","type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro"},{"type":"text","text":" unlocks a localized "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayoutProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for every locale in your license, and automatically injects them into the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/StandardProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" when a valid license key is registered.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro also unlocks more standard input sets, like QWERTZ and AZERTY, adds more capabilities to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and in general makes it a lot easier to work with layouts","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"More-Input-Sets","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"More Input Sets"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro unlocks more input sets, like "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet\/qwertz","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InputSet\/azerty"},{"type":"text","text":". These are used by some of the localized layouts, but you can use them separately as well."}]},{"level":3,"text":"More KeyboardLayout functionality","type":"heading","anchor":"More-KeyboardLayout-functionality"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro unlocks more ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout","isActive":true},{"text":" capabilities, like ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/adjusted(for:layoutConfiguration:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/copy()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/createIdealItem(for:width:alignment:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", which are used by some other Pro features."}]},{"anchor":"iPad-Pro-layout-support","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"iPad Pro layout support"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro unlocks an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayout\/iPadProProvider","isActive":true},{"text":" that can be used to generate iPad Pro-specific layouts. It’s used by some locales, and will be added to more locales over time.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Localized layout providers","level":3,"anchor":"Localized-layout-providers","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro unlocks a localized "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardLayoutProvider"},{"type":"text","text":" for every locale in your license."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can access any provider in your license like this:"}]},{"code":["let swedish = try KeyboardLayout.ProProvider.Swedish()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"These providers will throw a license error if their locale is not included in the license."}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How to customize a localized provider","anchor":"How-to-customize-a-localized-provider","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can inherit and customize any localized provider, then manually register your provider "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"after"}]},{"text":" registering your license key:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["class CustomProvider: KeyboardLayout.ProProvider.Swedish {","","    override func keyboardLayout(for context: KeyboardContext) -> KeyboardLayout {","        let provider = keyboardLayoutProvider(for: context)","        var layout = provider.keyboardLayout(for: context)","        guard let item = layout.tryCreateBottomRowItem(","            for: .character(\"🇸🇪\")","        ) else { return layout }","        layout.itemRows.insert(item, after: .space, atRow: layout.bottomRowIndex)","        return layout","    }","}","","class KeyboardController: KeyboardInputViewController {","","    override func viewWillSetupKeyboard() {","        super.viewWillSetupKeyboard()","","        setupPro(withLicenseKey: \"...\") { license in","            setupCustomProvider()","        } view: { controller in","            \/\/ Return your keyboard view here","        }","    }","","    func setupCustomProvider() {","        do {","            let provider = try CustomProvider()","            let standard = services.layoutProvider as? KeyboardLayout.StandardProvider","            standard?.registerLocalizedProvider(provider)","        } catch {","            print(error)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is useful for the cases when you want to make modifications to a single locale, but keep all other locales unaffected.","type":"text"}]}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Layout-Article"},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Features","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Essentials","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Actions-Article","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/AI-Article","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/App-Article","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardK